reviews.text:
If you love history and architecture  this is a great place to go. Unfortunately I was only there at night when all is closed but it was still a great place to see if somewhat at a distance. 
It is basically closed for restoration from what u could tell so I suggest checking when restoration is complete or at least complete enough for some part of it to be opened up and then visiting this place. 
It's truly beautiful.

A very humbling experience seeing such an old, beautiful castle in a state of ruin. If you stop by, there is a rest area at the entrance that has a donation box. If you have a few yen to spare I would highly recommend a small donation to contribute to the restoration of this historic site.

Excellent, a vast wide territory and when we arrived there was a Yosakoi festival going on. The castle is exceptionally beautiful, especially in spring time. Even after the earthquake, this is very much worth a visit, or even more visits.

5 points for the resilience and dedication to restoring this remarkable castle. And not only that, although you can't enter the buildings, the site has been set up to make it still a worthwhile visit. Lots of information in various languages.

Wish the castle will be renovated soon. So sad to see the rock, the debris of structures downs there.  Even though the great of man-made castle is still there. Worth to spending time walking around the place.
楽しい福島の名産品のお土産屋さんはオススメです！手作りの色んな物もありますしお菓子関係も豊富です。落ち葉のふかふかの林の中を散歩するのも良し、ジンギスカンで煙まみれになるもよし、ビール飲んでもジェラート食べるも良し！何しても楽しめる福島の定番スポットなのは間違いないと思います。

入場料はなく、とても周りは綺麗だし、散歩コースに良いかも。
自転車や、動物は❌らしいですよ。
久々に訪れました。雨上がりの日曜日でしたので混んでおりませんでしたが、一つ一つの施設が充実していて感心しました。庭園も芝生の広場も良く手入れが行き届いていて素晴らしいです。レストランのメニューも豊富で、とてもリーズナブルです。生ビールも美味しく頂きました。ファミリーユースには最適なところかと思いました。当日は、大人四人でワイワイ楽しみました。

広い敷地内には

体験施設の工芸館・農産物直売所（農家さんとれたて直売）があり他にも
農園レストラン・水車小屋もある

暑い夏場は入り口からすぐそこにある『じゃぶちゃぷ池』で子供たちを遊ばすにいかがでしょうか？

子供が安全に遊べるよう設計された池だそぅです。

園内はサラサラ流れる人工の川があり風流を味わえますよｗ

周りの景色も吾妻山が眺められ、自然観満喫できます(^_^;)

四季の郷というだけあって四季折々の植物が拝めるらしく

植物好きな方には堪らない施設じゃないでしょうか　笑

これで入園無料とは驚きです。

自信持ってオススメ出来る施設です
四季折々の景色を見ながら、散歩するのが気持ち良いですね。
Favorite place in Kumamoto. Quiet beautiful views of Kumamoto city. The history of the warlord Kato kiyomasa is very interesting
Beautiful area.

I have been in Japan for a long time, so temples and shrines don't seem that unique anymore, but the Honmyoji temple complex is really nice. You can really get a feel for traditional Japanese temples here.

長くゆるい坂道と階段が続く参道、上まで上がると加藤清正の銅像があり、熊本市内と熊本城が眺められます。
熊本地震があってからは参道の灯籠がすべて倒れ、今は少し立て直されていますが、まだその時の爪痕が所どころに見られます。それ以後、夏のとんしゃ（お祭り）は出店がなく華やかさにかけますが、最近は夜灯りや各所で小さなライブやお茶所があり、大人の祭りに様変わりしました。
この夜も桜灯りのイベントでしっとりと楽しむことができました。
夏のとんしゃの時は虫よけスプレーが必需品ですよー。

熊本市の街を一望できるスポットです。風光明媚で心が癒される私のお気に入りの場所。売店で買う昔ながらの瓶ソーダを飲みながら美しい自然を満喫してはいかがでしょうか？
個人的に熊本に観光に来られた方に一番足を運んでほしいスポットです。路面電車の「本妙寺前」から降りてすぐなのですが、けっこうな階段を上らなければいけません。その点は留意していただければと思います。本妙寺内には様々なお寺やお墓もあります。石畳みの道を歩いているとなんとも言えないノスタルジーを感じます。また、春は桜の隠れた名所だったりします。
このように魅力溢れる本妙寺にはぜひ一度足を運んでいただけたらと思います。
Best place for eating outdoor. There are many cherry blossom trees on the top of the mountain.
Best view to see the city

great view. very peaceful place.
It's pity tourists have to leave because the temple closes. However, thank the temple to open the parking for tourist like us :)
Great views over the massive expanse of Kumamoto. If you get a cab up, ask him nicely to wait for 10 minutes then take you back, otherwise you’re walking back.

Nice little uphill walk close from the Kumamoto station (20mins). View from there on the whole city definitely worth walk up couple of stairs. Or you can take a car and drive there as well. 
In the center is Buddhist Peace Pagoda remaining the victims of the World War II. 
There are many benches you can sit and relax.
great running area

熊本市内や有明海、雲仙の展望が抜群の山。
ほぼ山頂近くまで車で行くことができるので、夕焼けや夜景撮影に適しています。

友達と2回登頂しました。
初心者なのでとても時短で達成するので家族連れの方など気楽に登れるみたいです。
なんと言っても、下山後近くでlunchできることも楽しみの一つです。(*´∪`)

頂上の展望台から綺麗な熊本市の夜景を一望出来ます。
麓から一方通行の舗装された道路を車で登れます。
頂上近くには砂利敷きの駐車場があります（十数台くらい停められる）。そこから先は管理用道路になっていて「関係者以外進入禁止」とあり、車での進入は禁止になってます。しかし、展望台までを（2～300m？）徒歩で登るとなると、昼間はまだいいのですが夜は明かりも無く、女性は恐怖を感じるのではないでしょうか？もしくは、無断で車で頂上まで登るか、になります。
夜にここを訪れる時は注意が必要です。でも、夜景は綺麗ですよ。もちろん昼間の眺望も素晴らしいです。

金峰山にはかなり行ってませんが、この間、熊本城の写真を撮りに行った時にははるか遠くに見えてました。

さるすべりを登って行って、初日の出を見たことを思い出しました。

みなさんもさるすべりコースで頂上まで行くほうが面白いのでオススメします。

Creepy doesn't even begin to describe this remote temple. Surreal, mystical, hair-raising... This was by far the weirdest temple we visited. It was definitely worth the drive up, but I'll think twice before visiting this place at night.

This cave temple is straight out of indiana jones,  - we went on a rainy day which was actually perfect because there was noone else around and the light rain made it seem even more mystical and eerie. you pay around 300 yen at the door. theres some artefacts at the door in a glass case with supposedly dragon skin petrified and musashi's paddle/wooden sword which was used in a his famous final duel.   and as you walk through there are small carvings of 500 bhuddist monks that achieved enlightment then you walk some more and there is a cave where musashi meditated. this cave was used as mystical spot  in ancient times so predates most of the bhuddist period. definately reccomend going if your into seeing mystical surrreal places.
It's a great historical place if you favor Japan's greatest samurai, Miyamoto Musashi.
Book of five rings birth place
A historical place with a spirit

Ordered the recommended ramen set. 

Soup has strong garlic favour. Raw egg in the ramen can be substituted with Japanese style soft boiled egg.

The ramen has the local style, tons of garlic. The noodles are a bit thicker than usually in fukuoka. I recommend the one with eggs, if you don't like them raw like in the pictures you can ask the staff to give you boiled eggs instead. There is also a larger size available for a bit extra but beware, it was really large.

Great ramen in a small local setting, the taste for the ramen is quite strong and really good place to eat ramen for a quiet night out or with a small group with a drink. There are English menus for people who do not read or speak Japanese.
Friendly pricing, very pleasant staff, food great.
It's famous ramen shop in Kumamoto area.
Really nice plaza (MALL). For sure they keep it clean and fresh. Everytime I come for a walk to kill some time I always fine diferent decorations and diferent stores.
Pet Friendly
All you want in this place

Primer centro comercial de Jalisco con casi 50 años de antigüedad.  100% vigente y funcional con tiendas de prestigio y restaurantes.  Al atardecer se puede disfrutar del espectáculo de miles de pájaros que llegan a pasar la noche en los árboles del estacionamiento.

Un gran centro comercial de tradición en Guadalajara. Con diversas tiendas de autoservicio y tiendas especializadas en diferentes productos. Puedes encontrar casi todo lo que necesites y con acceso a todos los bolsillos...
You can enjoy hot and spicy curry and meet friendly Sri Lankan staff members here!
Great food. Be careful how spicy you order it though
They have delicious Sri Lanka curry with various level of spicy. The curry soup is made from coconut milk that give you very good taste.
The chief is very nice and they have some employees who talk in English which is very helpful. Highly recommend it
Delicious
nice place with delicious meal
Fast and cheap local restaurant
Fast and convenience, taste good, 24 hours

Fast, clean and good. You can eat as much rice as you want and that is a big plus. I'd
 recommend しょうが焼き定食。

Food tasted good, atmosphere was modern & nice, and you help yourself to as much tea, water, and white rice as you want. Plus, the prices were good & they have an English option on their machine that you order from.

If you love history and architecture  this is a great place to go. Unfortunately I was only there at night when all is closed but it was still a great place to see if somewhat at a distance. 
It is basically closed for restoration from what u could tell so I suggest checking when restoration is complete or at least complete enough for some part of it to be opened up and then visiting this place. 
It's truly beautiful.

Excellent, a vast wide territory and when we arrived there was a Yosakoi festival going on. The castle is exceptionally beautiful, especially in spring time. Even after the earthquake, this is very much worth a visit, or even more visits.

5 points for the resilience and dedication to restoring this remarkable castle. And not only that, although you can't enter the buildings, the site has been set up to make it still a worthwhile visit. Lots of information in various languages.

Wish the castle will be renovated soon. So sad to see the rock, the debris of structures downs there.  Even though the great of man-made castle is still there. Worth to spending time walking around the place.
